# Entry vs inception (copy)

- **User following / personal track** — Talk about **entry**: when the user enters, their entry, since they entered, “when you enter” in forms. Prefer natural phrasing; do **not** repeat the stiff phrase “entry date” in every label unless clarity needs it. The DB column remains `user_start_date`.

- **Model / strategy track** — Talk about **inception**: since inception, from inception, at inception. This is **not** the user’s entry.

- **Do not** mix these metaphors in the same sentence (e.g. do not describe the model’s curve using “your entry”).
